{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867213125,"sessionID":"ses_28611514fffeFkuK0ZyGHEguh4","part":{"id":"prt_d79ef2dce001G7F2zePKb6wUqC","messageID":"msg_d79ef1269001b17AAqGlekBAgj","sessionID":"ses_28611514fffeFkuK0ZyGHEguh4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-92255f1e565644ab884fbcaafb56329a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/agentd` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `pkg/agentd/doc.go` with package documentation\n20:   - Package name: `agentd`\n21:   - Description: Agentd idle cleanup controller for monitoring and cleaning idle agent runtime sessions\n22:   - Verification: `go doc ./pkg/agentd`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Define default constants in `defaults.go`\n25:   - `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval = 1 * time.Minute`\n26:   - `DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n27:   - File: `pkg/agentd/defaults.go`\n28:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n29: \n30: - [ ] **T1.3**: Define `IdleCleanupStats` struct for stats retrieval\n31:   - Fields: `Interval time.Duration`, `IdleTimeout time.Duration`, `LastCleanupTime time.Time`\n32:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n33:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n34: \n35: ### Phase 2: IdleCleanupController Struct & Constructor (ST-2)\n36: \n37: - [ ] **T2.1**: Define `IdleCleanupController` struct with all required fields\n38:   - `store Store` — for session state lookup\n39:   - `lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager` — for sandbox deletion delegation\n40:   - `interval time.Duration` — for cleanup check interval\n41:   - `idleTimeout time.Duration` — for idle threshold\n42:   - `stopCh chan struct{}` — for graceful shutdown signal\n43:   - `wg sync.WaitGroup` — for goroutine synchronization\n44:   - `logger Logger` — for structured logging\n45:   - `idleMu sync.RWMutex` — protects `idleTimeout` for thread-safe access\n46:   - `lastCleanupTime time.Time` — tracks last cleanup cycle\n47:   - `lastCleanupMu sync.RWMutex` — protects `lastCleanupTime`\n48:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n49:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor\n52:   - Signature: `NewIdleCleanupController(store Store, lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager, interval, idleTimeout time.Duration, logger Logger) *IdleCleanupController`\n53:   - Apply defaults: if `interval == 0`, use `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval`\n54:   - Apply defaults: if `idleTimeout == 0`, use `DefaultIdleTimeout`\n55:   - Initialize `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n56:   - Validate non-nil store, lifecycleManager, logger\n57:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n58:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v`\n59: \n60: ### Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods (ST-3)\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `Start()` method\n63:   - Call `ctrl.wg.Add(1)`\n64:   - Launch `go ctrl.runLoop()`\n65:   - Non-blocking, returns immediately\n66:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n67:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `Stop()` method\n70:   - Call `close(ctrl.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n71:   - Call `ctrl.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n72:   - Returns only after goroutine exits\n73:   - Safe to call multiple times (idempotent via sync.Once or nil check)\n74:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n75:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `runLoop()` background ticker loop\n78:   - Run in separate goroutine (started by `Start()`)\n79:   - Execute `ctrl.runOnce(context.Background())` immediately on start\n80:   - Create `ticker := time.NewTicker(ctrl.interval)`\n81:   - Loop on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n82:   - On `stopCh`: log `\"idle cleanup controller stopped\"` and return\n83:   - On `ticker.C`: call `ctrl.runOnce(context.Background())`\n84:   - Defer `ctrl.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n85:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n86:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n87: \n88: ### Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic (ST-4)\n89: \n90: - [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` — session listing\n91:   - Call `ctrl.store.ListSessions(ctx)` to get all active sessions\n92:   - Log error if list fails: `\"failed to list sessions\"`\n93:   - Return error if list fails\n94:   - Iterate all sessions for idle check\n95:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n96:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_ListSessions -v`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T4.2**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` — idle status check\n99:   - For each session, check `time.Now().Sub(session.LastActivity)`\n100:   - Skip session if `LastActivity.IsZero() == true` (no activity recorded)\n101:   - Mark session as idle if `duration > ctrl.getIdleTimeout()`\n102:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n103:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_IdleSession -v`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` — cleanup execution\n106:   - For idle sessions: call `ctrl.lifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, session.SessionID)`\n107:   - Pass deletion reason as `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n108:   - Handle `NotFoundError`: silently ignore (already deleted), continue\n109:   - Handle other errors: log `\"idle cleanup failed\"` with sessionID and err, continue\n110:   - Log successful cleanup: `\"idle cleanup deleted session\"` with sessionID, idleDuration, reason\n111:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n112:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_Cleanup -v`\n113: \n114: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` — completion logging\n115:   - Track count of cleaned sessions\n116:   - Update `lastCleanupTime` to `time.Now()` after cycle completes\n117:   - Log: `\"idle cleanup cycle completed\"` with `cleanedCount`\n118:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n119:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_Completion -v`\n120: \n121: ### Phase 5: Runtime Configuration Methods (ST-5)\n122: \n123: - [ ] **T5.1**: Implement `SetIdleTimeout(timeout)` method\n124:   - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.Lock()`\n125:   - Update `ctrl.idleTimeout`\n126:   - Release mutex\n127:   - Thread-safe for concurrent access\n128:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n129:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `GetIdleTimeout()` method\n132:   - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.RLock()`\n133:   - Return current `ctrl.idleTimeout`\n134:   - Release mutex\n135:   - Thread-safe for concurrent reads\n136:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n137:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_GetIdleTimeout -v`\n138: \n139: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `GetStats()` stats retrieval method\n140:   - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.RLock()` and `ctrl.lastCleanupMu.RLock()`\n141:   - Return `IdleCleanupStats{Interval, IdleTimeout, LastCleanupTime}`\n142:   - Release mutexes\n143:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n144:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_GetStats -v`\n145: \n146: ### Phase 6: Concurrent Safety (ST-6)\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T6.1**: Implement thread-safe `idleTimeout` access\n149:   - Add `idleMu sync.RWMutex` to `IdleCleanupController` struct\n150:   - Protect all reads via `getIdleTimeout()` internal method\n151:   - Protect all writes via `SetIdleTimeout()`\n152:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n153:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T6.2**: Implement thread-safe `lastCleanupTime` access\n156:   - Add `lastCleanupMu sync.RWMutex` to `IdleCleanupController` struct\n157:   - Protect writes in `runOnce()` via `lastCleanupMu.Lock()`\n158:   - Protect reads in `GetStats()` via `lastCleanupMu.RLock()`\n159:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n160:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n161: \n162: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T7.1**: Test `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor\n165:   - Test: constructor returns valid instance\n166:   - Test: custom interval and timeout are set correctly\n167:   - Test: default values applied when parameters are zero\n168:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n169:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v`\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test `Start()` and `Stop()` lifecycle\n172:   - Test: `Start()` launches goroutine\n173:   - Test: `Stop()` completes without hanging\n174:   - Test: goroutine exits cleanly\n175:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n176:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n177: \n178: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test `runOnce()` idle session detection\n179:   - Test: idle session (LastActivity > idleTimeout ago) is cleaned\n180:   - Test: active session (LastActivity < idleTimeout ago) remains\n181:   - Test: session with zero LastActivity is skipped\n182:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n183:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_IdleSession -v`\n184: \n185: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test `runOnce()` error handling\n186:   - Test: all sessions processed even if some cleanups fail\n187:   - Test: NotFound errors silently ignored\n188:   - Test: other errors logged but don't stop cycle\n189:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n190:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T7.5**: Test `SetIdleTimeout()` and `GetIdleTimeout()`\n193:   - Test: `SetIdleTimeout()` updates threshold correctly\n194:   - Test: `GetIdleTimeout()` returns updated value\n195:   - Test: `GetStats()` reflects updated timeout\n196:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n197:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v`\n198: \n199: - [ ] **T7.6**: Test concurrent access safety\n200:   - Test: no race conditions on `SetIdleTimeout()` concurrent access\n201:   - Test: no race conditions on `GetStats()` concurrent access\n202:   - Test: no race conditions during `runOnce()` with config changes\n203:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n204:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n205: \n206: ### Phase 8: Integration & Validation (ST-8)\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T8.1**: Verify Store interface integration\n209:   - `store.ListSessions(ctx)` returns `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n210:   - Sessions include `SessionID` and `LastActivity` fields\n211:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n212:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StoreIntegration -v`\n213: \n214: - [ ] **T8.2**: Verify SandboxLifecycleManager integration\n215:   - `lifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` handles K8s sandbox CR and store cleanup\n216:   - Deletion reason is `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n217:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n218:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_LifecycleIntegration -v`\n219: \n220: - [ ] **T8.3**: All unit tests pass with coverage\n221:   - `go test ./pkg/agentd -v` passes all tests\n222:   - Coverage: >80% for `idle_cleanup.go`\n223:   - No race conditions: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race`\n224:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n225:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out`\n226: \n227: - [ ] **T8.4**: Lint and build verification\n228:   - `go vet ./pkg/agentd` passes with zero issues\n229:   - `golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/...` passes\n230:   - `go build ./pkg/agentd` succeeds\n231:   - File: `pkg/agentd/`\n232:   - Verification: `go vet ./pkg/agentd && golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/... && go build ./pkg/agentd`\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ## Task Dependencies\n237: \n238: ```\n239: T1.1 → T1.2 → T1.3\n240:          ↓\n241:        T2.1 → T2.2\n242:               ↓\n243:        T3.1 → T3.2 → T3.3\n244:               ↓\n245:        T4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3 → T4.4\n246:               ↓\n247:        T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3\n248:               ↓\n249:        T6.1 → T6.2\n250:               ↓\n251:        T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3 → T7.4 → T7.5 → T7.6\n252:               ↓\n253:        T8.1 → T8.2 → T8.3 → T8.4\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Verification Commands\n259: \n260: | Task | Verification Command |\n261: |------|----------------------|\n262: | All tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -v` |\n263: | Constructor tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v` |\n264: | Lifecycle tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v` |\n265: | Cleanup tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce -v` |\n266: | Config tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v` |\n267: | Concurrent safety | `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v` |\n268: | Test coverage | `go test ./pkg/agentd -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out \\| grep idle_cleanup` |\n269: | Build verification | `go build ./pkg/agentd` |\n270: | Lint check | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/...` |\n271: | Vet check | `go vet ./pkg/agentd` |\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## Acceptance Criteria\n276: \n277: - [ ] `IdleCleanupController` struct defined with all required fields\n278: - [ ] `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor with default fallbacks\n279: - [ ] `Start()` launches background goroutine\n280: - [ ] `Stop()` signals shutdown and waits for completion\n281: - [ ] `runLoop()` uses ticker for periodic execution\n282: - [ ] `runOnce()` checks session idle status via `LastActivity`\n283: - [ ] Sessions with zero `LastActivity` skipped\n284: - [ ] Idle sessions trigger `DeleteSandbox` delegation\n285: - [ ] NotFound errors silently ignored\n286: - [ ] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n287: - [ ] `SetIdleTimeout()` runtime configuration supported\n288: - [ ] `GetIdleTimeout()` returns current timeout\n289: - [ ] `GetStats()` returns current configuration and last cleanup time\n290: - [ ] Default constants defined: `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval=1m`, `DefaultIdleTimeout=15m`\n291: - [ ] Store `ListSessions()` method used for session lookup\n292: - [ ] `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox()` used for cleanup\n293: - [ ] `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` logged for observability\n294: - [ ] Unit tests cover idle/active/zero scenarios\n295: - [ ] Unit tests cover Start/Stop lifecycle\n296: - [ ] Package structure follows agentcube conventions\n297: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n298: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n299: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## File Changes Summary\n304: \n305: | File | Action | Lines Changed | Description |\n306: |------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n307: | `pkg/agentd/doc.go` | Create | ~10 | Package documentation for agentd module |\n308: | `pkg/agentd/defaults.go` | Create | ~15 | `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval`, `DefaultIdleTimeout` constants |\n309: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` | Create | ~150 | `IdleCleanupController`, `NewIdleCleanupController`, `Start`, `Stop`, `runLoop`, `runOnce`, `SetIdleTimeout`, `GetIdleTimeout`, `GetStats`, `getIdleTimeout`, `IdleCleanupStats` |\n310: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` | Create | ~350 | Comprehensive unit tests (6 test groups, ~15 test cases) |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Implementation Notes\n315: \n316: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n317: - **Reference implementation**: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` provides similar pattern\n318: - **Thread-safe implementation**: Use `sync.RWMutex` for `idleTimeout` and `lastCleanupTime` fields\n319: - **Graceful degradation**: Cleanup continues processing even if individual deletions fail\n320: - **Immediate execution**: First cleanup runs immediately on `Start()`, then periodic via ticker\n321: - **Integration points**:\n322:   - `pkg/workloadmanager` — `SandboxLifecycleManager`, `Store`, `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`, `Logger`\n323:   - `pkg/common/types` — `SandboxInfo` struct with `LastActivity` field\n324: - **Key differences from GarbageCollector**:\n325:   - Uses `ListSessions()` instead of `ListExpiredSandboxes()`/`ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n326:   - Filters idle sessions client-side based on `LastActivity` comparison\n327:   - No batch size limit (processes all sessions)\n328:   - Tracks `LastCleanupTime` for observability\n329: \n330: ---\n331: \n332: ## Implementation Timeline\n333: \n334: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n335: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n336: | Phase 1: Core Types & Constants | T1.1, T1.2, T1.3 | Pending | 0% |\n337: | Phase 2: Struct & Constructor | T2.1, T2.2 | Pending | 0% |\n338: | Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods | T3.1, T3.2, T3.3 | Pending | 0% |\n339: | Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic | T4.1, T4.2, T4.3, T4.4 | Pending | 0% |\n340: | Phase 5: Runtime Config | T5.1, T5.2, T5.3 | Pending | 0% |\n341: | Phase 6: Concurrent Safety | T6.1, T6.2 