{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867347464,"sessionID":"ses_28611514fffeFkuK0ZyGHEguh4","part":{"id":"prt_d79f1419b001bMa3mg4LuA8X43","messageID":"msg_d79ef6639001Lieeea4fPK5RF4","sessionID":"ses_28611514fffeFkuK0ZyGHEguh4","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-39188d730c574e57b971a12785806266","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md","content":"# AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) |\n| Module | `cmd` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Shared CLI Infrastructure (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/version.go` with version constants\n  - Define `Version = \"0.1.0\"`\n  - Define `GitCommit` (populated at build time)\n  - Define `BuildDate` (populated at build time)\n  - File: `cmd/internal/cli/version.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/flagset.go` with common flag handling\n  - Define `FlagSet` struct for common CLI flags\n  - Include `Verbose`, `Kubeconfig`, `Namespace` flags\n  - Define `BindFlags(fs *flag.FlagSet)` method\n  - File: `cmd/internal/cli/flagset.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n\n- [ ] **T1.3**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/logging.go` with klog initialization\n  - Define `InitLogging(verbose bool)` function\n  - Call `klog.InitFlags(nil)` and set `logtostderr=true`\n  - Set verbose level based on flag\n  - File: `cmd/internal/cli/logging.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n\n- [ ] **T1.4**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/signal.go` with signal handling\n  - Define `SetupSignalHandler() context.Context`\n  - Handle SIGTERM, SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n  - Return cancelable context\n  - File: `cmd/internal/cli/signal.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n\n### Phase 2: agentcube CLI Binary (ST-2)\n\n- [ ] **T2.1**: Create `cmd/agentcube/main.go` skeleton\n  - Package: `main`\n  - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentcube`\n  - Define `main()` function\n  - Setup flag parsing with common flags\n  - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentcube`\n\n- [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `--version` flag handling in agentcube\n  - Add `-v`, `--version` flag\n  - Print version info: `AgentCube CLI version: {Version}, commit: {GitCommit}`\n  - Exit 0 after printing version\n  - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n  - Verification: `./bin/agentcube --version`\n\n- [ ] **T2.3**: Implement agentcube subcommand structure\n  - Define subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`\n  - Use `flag.NewFlagSet` for each subcommand\n  - Print usage help on invalid subcommand\n  - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n  - Verification: `./bin/agentcube --help`\n\n- [ ] **T2.4**: Add agentcube help and usage documentation\n  - Define command help text\n  - Implement `printUsage()` function\n  - Add example usage in help output\n  - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n  - Verification: `./bin/agentcube`\n\n### Phase 3: agentd Daemon Binary (ST-3)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1**: Create `cmd/agentd/main.go` skeleton\n  - Package: `main`\n  - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentd`\n  - Define `main()` function\n  - Setup flag parsing\n  - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2**: Define agentd configuration flags\n  - `--port` (int, default 8081): HTTP listening port\n  - `--router-url` (string): Router service URL\n  - `--workload-manager-url` (string): WorkloadManager URL\n  - `--idle-cleanup-interval` (duration, default 1m): Cleanup interval\n  - `--idle-timeout` (duration, default 15m): Session idle timeout\n  - `--kubeconfig` (string): Kubernetes config path\n  - `--namespace` (string, default \"default\"): Kubernetes namespace\n  - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n\n- [ ] **T3.3**: Initialize agentd dependencies\n  - Create Kubernetes client from kubeconfig\n  - Initialize Redis/Valkey store client\n  - Create `SandboxLifecycleManager` instance\n  - Create `IdleCleanupController` instance\n  - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n\n- [ ] **T3.4**: Implement agentd server startup\n  - Call `IdleCleanupController.Start()`\n  - Setup signal handler for graceful shutdown\n  - Wait for shutdown signal\n  - Call `IdleCleanupController.Stop()` on exit\n  - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentd -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.5**: Add agentd version flag\n  - Add `--version` flag\n  - Print version and exit\n  - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n  - Verification: `./bin/agentd --version`\n\n### Phase 4: agentsandbox Runtime Binary (ST-4)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1**: Create `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go` skeleton\n  - Package: `main`\n  - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentsandbox`\n  - Define `main()` function\n  - Follow pattern from `cmd/picod/main.go`\n  - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2**: Define agentsandbox configuration flags\n  - `--port` (int, default 8080): HTTP listening port\n  - `--workspace` (string): Workspace directory path\n  - `--session-id` (string): Current session ID\n  - `--sandbox-id` (string): Sandbox identifier\n  - `--entrypoint` (string): Agent entrypoint command\n  - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n\n- [ ] **T4.3**: Integrate agentsandbox with picod package\n  - Import `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod`\n  - Create `picod.Config` from flags\n  - Create `picod.NewServer(config)`\n  - Call `server.Run(ctx)`\n  - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n\n- [ ] **T4.4**: Implement agentsandbox graceful shutdown\n  - Setup signal handler (SIGTERM, SIGINT)\n  - Pass cancelable context to server\n  - Log shutdown message\n  - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentsandbox -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.5**: Add agentsandbox version flag\n  - Add `--version` flag\n  - Print version and exit\n  - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n  - Verification: `./bin/agentsandbox --version`\n\n### Phase 5: agentctl Control Tool Binary (ST-5)\n\n- [ ] **T5.1**: Create `cmd/agentctl/main.go` skeleton\n  - Package: `main`\n  - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentctl`\n  - Define `main()` function\n  - Setup flag parsing\n  - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n\n- [ ] **T5.2**: Define agentctl global flags\n  - `--kubeconfig` (string): Kubernetes config path\n  - `--namespace` (string, default \"default\"): Kubernetes namespace\n  - `--output` (string, default \"table\"): Output format (table, json, yaml)\n  - `--verbose` (bool): Enable verbose output\n  - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n\n- [ ] **T5.3**: Implement agentctl `list` subcommand\n  - List all AgentRuntime CRs in namespace\n  - Output: name, status, endpoint, age\n  - Support table/json/yaml output formats\n  - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n  - Verification: `./bin/agentctl list --namespace=default`\n\n- [ ] **T5.4**: Implement agentctl `get` subcommand\n  - Get specific AgentRuntime by name\n  - Show detailed status information\n  - Support json/yaml output\n  - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n  - Verification: `./bin/agentctl get my-agent`\n\n- [ ] **T5.5**: Implement agentctl `delete` subcommand\n  - Delete AgentRuntime by name\n  - Support `--force` flag for immediate deletion\n  - Support `--wait` flag to wait for deletion\n  - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n\n- [ ] **T5.6**: Implement agentctl `status` subcommand\n  - Check session status for an agent\n  - Show active sessions count\n  - Show last activity time\n  - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n\n- [ ] **T5.7**: Add agentctl version flag and help\n  - Add `--version` flag\n  - Print version and exit\n  - Implement usage help\n  - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n  - Verification: `./bin/agentctl --version`\n\n### Phase 6: Build Configuration (ST-6)\n\n- [ ] **T6.1**: Create Makefile with build targets\n  - `build-agentcube`: Build agentcube binary\n  - `build-agentd`: Build agentd binary\n  - `build-agentsandbox`: Build agentsandbox binary\n  - `build-agentctl`: Build agentctl binary\n  - `build-all`: Build all binaries\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verification: `make build-all`\n\n- [ ] **T6.2**: Add ldflags for version injection\n  - `-X main.Version=$(VERSION)`\n  - `-X main.GitCommit=$(GIT_COMMIT)`\n  - `-X main.BuildDate=$(BUILD_DATE)`\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verification: `make build-agentcube && ./bin/agentcube --version`\n\n- [ ] **T6.3**: Create Dockerfile for each binary\n  - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentcube\n  - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentd\n  - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentsandbox\n  - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentctl\n  - File: `build/Dockerfile.agentcube`, `build/Dockerfile.agentd`, etc.\n  - Verification: `docker build -f build/Dockerfile.agentcube -t agentcube .`\n\n- [ ] **T6.4**: Add install target in Makefile\n  - `install`: Copy binaries to `/usr/local/bin`\n  - Support `PREFIX` variable for custom install path\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verification: `make install PREFIX=/tmp/test && /tmp/test/bin/agentcube --version`\n\n### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n\n- [ ] **T7.1**: Test agentcube CLI version output\n  - Test: `--version` flag prints correct version format\n  - Test: exits with code 0\n  - File: `cmd/agentcube/main_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentcube -run TestVersion -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.2**: Test agentcube CLI help output\n  - Test: `--help` prints usage information\n  - Test: